title: Nearly 1 in 5 mail-in ballots in Houston area were rejected because of Texas voting law, election officials say - CNN
content:
1. Nearly 1 in 5 mail-in ballots in Houston area were rejected because of Texas voting law, election officials say  CNN
  2. Texas Flagged 27000 Mail Ballots For Rejection During Primary  NBC News
  3. At least 18000 Texas mail-in votes were rejected in the first election under new GOP voting rules  The Texas Tribune
  4. Votes of over 18,000 urban Texans were tossed because of new elections law  Houston Chronicle
  5. Tarrant County sees hundreds more rejected mail-in ballots than it did in 2018  Fort Worth Star-Telegram
description: Thousands of mail-in ballots were rejected in Texas' most populous county for the March primary because they did not meet requirements set by the state's new voting law passed last year by the Republican-led state legislature, according to Houston-area election officials.
